post_text:
Show your Trojan Pride!
West Marshall After Prom has
WM Trojan Facemasks for sale!
West Marshall After Prom is selling WM Trojan face masks as a fundraiser to support a fun and safe After Prom for West Marshall students. There are both youth and adult masks. There will be no returns or exchanges. No extra masks will be ordered.

Here is the link to the online store:
https://westmarshallfacemask2020.itemorder.com/
Please note that it says that orders must be placed in bulk (of 10), but that is not the case. You can order fewer than 10.
We will be taking online orders through Sunday, September 20th. Orders will be delivered 2-4 weeks after the store closes.
If you have any questions, please email Theresa Siegert at thesiegert6@gmail.com.
Thank you for your support of WM After Prom.

Questions? Contact
Theresa Siegert at thesiegert6@gmail.com

This message is for the 6th-8th grade parents. You should of gotten an email from JMC but wanted to share here also.

Happy First Friday of the new school year. This year we are changing our weekly newsletter that we send home. The link we give you is always on our school website, under Schools, then click on middle school and on the left you will see Announcements/Newsletters. Click on that and it will take you to our new paper. As you can see on the left you can click for the daily announcements and on the right is the newsletter. The newsletter is done by grade levels and then classes. You can click on the class of your child and see what the teacher has to say. Not all teachers may have something yet, but check back the next week. It has been great to have all the kids back this week. Have a great weekend.

https://sites.google.com/wmcsd.org/wm-middle-school-news/home

Click on that and it will take you to our new paper. As you can see on the left you can click for the daily announcements and on the right is the newsletter. The newsletter is done by grade levels and then classes. You can click on the class of your child and see what the teacher has to say. Not all teachers may have something yet, but check back the next week. It has been great to have all the kids back this week. Have a great weekend.

https://sites.google.com/wmcsd.org/wm-middle-school-news/home

post_text:
For those of you attending tonight’s football game here are the guidelines. Gate opens at 6:15.

Guidelines:

1. Every other row will be blocked off. Do not sit on the rows (or areas) with blue tape.
The large visitor bleachers are for West Marshall, Gilbert will use the small set.
2. Please social distance from other families. Masks are recommended in common
areas (ticket booth, the concessions line, etc.)
3. There will be no standing on the fence. All fans need to be in the stands.
4. We will have a VERY limited concession stand: drinks, candy and chips.
5. As soon as the game is over, please exit the stadium.

post_text:
Please Welcome Nicole Wilson.
Hi! My name is Nicole Wilson, and I am the new nurse for the district. I currently live in Altoona with my husband Blake and our dogs (Bailey and JoJo). I have been a nurse for a little over a year with mainly working in a pediatric clinic. I have a Bachelor's Degree in Communication Studies from The University of Iowa (Go Hawkeyes!) and I have my ASN from Iowa Lakes CC in Emmetsburg, IA. In my free time I like to spend time with my family, go shopping, play golf, and cheer on the Hawkeyes! I am excited to start this school year at West Marshall and see all the new adventures we will come across.

West Marshall’s Return to Learn is Just DAYS Away!

AUGUST 24, 2020 (Full-Time)

We have finalized our information Pamphlet that allows Families, Students and Staff to access a one-stop shop for guidance to start-out the year with. Principal’s will be communicating with families regarding specifics for each of their buildings regarding logistics.

We thank each of you for your input and support while we hit the ground running during this unique start-up to the 2020 school year. We are excited to welcome everyone back! More than you can imagine... It has been way to long without working and doing what we crave each day as educators, and that's teaching and learning with and for your children.

Thank you for allowing us this opportunity!https://drive.google.com/file/d/1pihvHtZuuPkvf9OfkKeWkgwhP_7r1dW-/view?usp=sharing

post_text:
Good morning West Marshall Community,
We would like to welcome Rebecca Roberts to the West Marshall family. Rebecca will be teaching 6th and 7th grade science this year at the middle school. Welcome to West Marshall!

My name is Rebecca Roberts and I am excited to be teaching 6th and 7th Grade Science at West Marshall
this year. I have previously taught high school science. I have also worked for the ISU Extension Office
and have been a paraeducator. I got my Bachelor of Science in Animal Ecology and Forestry at ISU and
my teaching license at BVU. Outside of school, I like going for walks, playing board games, and reading.
One of my favorite books when I was in Middle School was Ella Enchanted by Gail Carson Levine. I still
like reading fairy tales and am currently reading A Thousand Beginnings and Endings, which is an
anthology of retold fairy tales edited by Ellen Oh and Elise Chapman. I also enjoy spending time with my
family and over break have been learning embroidery.
I am excited for school to start and am looking forward to meeting everyone soon.

post_text:
Message from Mr. Large in regards to school board meetings and still offering Zoom meetings to everyone in the district to be involved with what is going on.

Meetings have been open onsite for the last three meetings. We are glad to offer zoom to keep more folks involved, where in the past 1-4 people would show up. If we have a lot of people we can host in the auditorium, however if anyone wants to speak we answer questions puplically in the chat room on zoom and also in person. All board members attend in person, except for Sue which is simply due to being gone for work. Shawn has her reasons. Hope this helps with the questions. Thanks.

post_text: Trojan baseball has officially come to an end tonight. The ruling is enough innings had been played so game over. Score was 2-3 in the middle of the 6th. We would like to thank our Seniors of Gabe, Jake and Jeremy for your dedication to the team this year and wish you the best of luck. 2020 Baseball season has been one for the books dealing with a shortened season thanks to Covid-19. Thankful our kids all stayed healthy and got to play and have the awesome 5 walk off wins. Congratulations and good luck with your future endeavors. To the rest of team we will see you all back next year for a full season!

WEST MARSHALL CROSS COUNTRY CAMP

For athletes in Grades 7th - 12th

The West Marshall Cross Country Coaches will work with your athletes on a variety of aspects of the sport including
warming up and stretching, endurance, speed work,
hill work, cooling down and post-workout stretching, goal setting, hydration, and nutrition. This will be a fun, educational experience for any level of athlete. Just wear shorts and t-shirt, bring a watch, and water or Gatorade/Powerade.

Dates: August 3 - August 7
Time: 7:30 a.m. to 9:00 a.m.

Registration:Free
Mail the completed form by July 31 or bring to camp on Aug. 3

West Marshall Cross Country
℅ Cynthia Hilleman
PO Box 670, 601 3rd Street NW
State Center, IA 50247

Questions Contact: chilleman@wmcsd.org or 641-483-2136

Today is our official last day of school for the 2019/20 school year! Although things did not end as planned, we appreciate all WM has done for our students, especially the last few months. Each educator has played a key role in the lives of our students.

Please take a moment to enjoy this year's 8th grade recognition to the 2024 class!

Attached is the 8th grade graduation document which includes: The 8th grade slideshow, memory book, video, collage, and messages from staff. Click on each individual picture to access the links.

Our 8th grade virtual recognition would not have been possible without the help from Mrs. Haley, Mrs. Wison, Mr. Randall and our 8th grade Student Council members. Thank you all for your dedication during this time.

Have a wonderful summer and stay safe!

Please see attachment.

Sincerely,

Ms. Kriegel

Our 8th grade virtual recognition would not have been possible without the help from Mrs. Haley, Mrs. Wison, Mr. Randall and our 8th grade Student Council members. Thank you all for your dedication during this time.

Have a wonderful summer and stay safe!

Please see attachment.

Sincerely,

Ms. Kriegel

West Marshall FFA
May 3 at 11:35 AM ·

Greenhouse Plant Sale: The West Marshall FFA will have our annual plant sale this Thursday and Friday from 1pm to 6pm each day in the parking lot between the High school and middle school. The school closing has prompted us to do a different kind of sale this year. We will be asking for a free-will donation for the plants you select. We also ask that only 5 people at a time selecting plants. This is in accordance with State Center ordinance due to the COVID-19. We will be offering hanging baskets including ivy geranium, various colored petunia, bridal veil, and fuchsia. We also will have a selection of annual bedding plants available.

post_text: Attention Juniors & Seniors! Yearbook is working hard on putting together the yearbook. The request right now is for any Junior or Senior to dress up in your best and have a parent take your picture and send to them. So put that dress or suit, shirt and blue jeans on and take a fun picture of yourself and send it in. post_text:
Great Job!
The LUCC philanthropy group consisting of members of WMCSD high school students provided a grant opportunity that couldn't be passed up by the MS/HS Art Department! Students create the most amazing visual works of art that with photography can be recorded and shared with others. The professionalism of how the images are captured is what Mrs. Sogge was hoping to gain through the grant opportunity. The LUCC members in conjunction with the Community Foundation of Marshall County~CFMC have provided the art program with monies to purchase equipment, such as backdrops, LED lighting and bounce reflectors. The specialized equipment will allow the art program to continue its path of digital professionalism for documenting students' works of art for competitions, college scholarship portfolios and digital portfolio evaluations.
Thank you LUCC for this grant honor! Mrs. Sogge
